<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1436,907,1077]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">
<bibRefCitation author="Schiner, I. R." box="[151,374,907,934]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" refId="ref21511" refString="Schiner, I. R. (1862) Fauna Austriaca. Die Fliegen (Diptera). Nach einer analytischen Methode bearbeitet mit der Characteristik sammtlicher europaischer Gattungen, der Beschreibung aller in Deutschland vorkommenden Arten und der Aufzahlung aller bisher beschriebenen europaischen Arten. Erster Theil. Verlag von Carl Gerold's Sohn, Wien, 674 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8525" type="book" year="1862">Schiner (1862: 362)</bibRefCitation>
documented this species as “pretty mean and widespread; in wet meadows (…)”. The only “recent” records dates back to 1990 (
<collectingRegion box="[534,700,943,969]" country="Austria" name="Niederoesterreich" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Lower Austria</collectingRegion>
, Scheibbs, Schlagerboden; (
<specimenCount box="[1019,1054,943,969]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
) leg. Franz Ressl). The host plant of the larvae is the highly-local Asteraceae 
<emphasis box="[639,855,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Scorzonera humilis</emphasis>
L. (
<bibRefCitation author="Johansson, N." box="[902,1087,979,1005]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="5 - 10" refId="ref20123" refString="Johansson, N. (2011) Aterfynd av rodhornig manblomfluga Eumerus ruficornis Meigen, 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae) med noteringar kring artens ekologi. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 132, 5 - 10." type="journal article" year="2011">Johansson 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Due to the extreme loss of its habitat, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1822" box="[242,459,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Eumerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficornis">
<emphasis box="[242,459,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">Eumerus ruficornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to extinction in Central and northern Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Ssymank, A. &amp; Doczkal, D. &amp; Rennwald, K. &amp; Dziock, F." box="[1074,1309,1015,1042]" pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="13 - 83" refId="ref22510" refString="Ssymank, A., Doczkal, D., Rennwald, K. &amp; Dziock, F. (2011) Rote Liste und Gesamtartenliste der Schwebfliegen (Diptera Syrphidae) Deutschlands. In: Binot-Hafke, M., Balzer, S., Becker, N., Gruttke, H., Haupt, H., Hofbauer, N., Ludwig, G., Matzke-Hajek, G. &amp; Strauch, M. (Eds.), Rote Liste gefahrdeter Tiere, Pflanzen und Pilze Deutschlands. Band 3 Wirbellose Tiere. Teil 1. Naturschutz und Biologische Vielfalt. 70 (3). Landwirtschaftsverlag, Munster, pp. 13 - 83." type="book chapter" year="2011">
Ssymank 
<emphasis box="[1186,1236,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="170">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Johansson, N." pageId="19" pageNumber="170" pagination="5 - 10" refId="ref20123" refString="Johansson, N. (2011) Aterfynd av rodhornig manblomfluga Eumerus ruficornis Meigen, 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae) med noteringar kring artens ekologi. Entomologisk Tidskrift, 132, 5 - 10." type="journal article" year="2011">Johansson 2011</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
